-- Zimbabwe's Mugabe Threatens to Seize the Assets of U.S., British Companies
-- B y   N e l s o n   B a n y a
-- 2010-12-17T11:31:08Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-17/zimbabwe-s-mugabe-threatens-to-seize-the-assets-of-u-s-british-companies.html
Zimbabwe will seize 100 percent of
British and U.S. companies operating in the country, including
mining companies, unless their governments remove sanctions,
Zimbabwe’s President Robert Mugabe said in a speech in Mutare
today.  Mugabe was speaking at the ruling Zimbabwe African National
Union-Patriotic Front’s congress.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nelson Gore Banya in Johannesburg at 
 ngbanya@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
